  "prompt": "How long should a short story be?",
  "response": "A short story is typically defined as a work of fiction that is between 1,000 and 20,000 words long. However, the ideal length for a short story can vary depending on the specific requirements of the publication or contest you are submitting to, as well as the pacing and content of the story itself. Some short stories can be as brief as 500 words, while others can stretch to the upper limit of 20,000 words. In general, most short stories fall somewhere between 3,000 and 7,500 words.",
